---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy — BracketMath"
  description="BracketMath uses no cookies, no tracking pixels, and no personal data collection. Calculator inputs stay in your browser. Read the full privacy policy."
>
  <section class="px-6 pt-16 pb-10">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl">
      <p class="font-mono text-sm uppercase tracking-widest text-[color:var(--color-ink-light)] mb-4">
        Privacy
      </p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold tracking-tight text-[color:var(--color-ink)] leading-tight mb-6">
        No cookies. No tracking. Your numbers never leave your browser.
      </h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-[color:var(--color-ink-light)] leading-relaxed">
        BracketMath is built on the principle that you should be able to model your own tax and retirement
        scenarios without anyone — including us — ever seeing the inputs. This page explains exactly what
        data is and isn't collected, by whom, and for what purpose.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="px-6 py-12 border-t border-[color:var(--color-rule)]">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl prose">
      <h2>The short version</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>No cookies are set on this site.</li>
        <li>No personal data is collected, stored, or transmitted from any calculator.</li>
        <li>All calculations run entirely in your browser using JavaScript. Inputs (your salary, dividend, pension, age, etc.) are never sent to a server.</li>
        <li>We use Cloudflare Web Analytics — a privacy-preserving, cookieless analytics service — to count anonymous page views.</li>
        <li>No newsletter sign-up, no contact form, no account creation is currently offered. If we add any of these later, this page will be updated and the change noted explicitly.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>1. Data controller</h2>
      <p>
        For the purposes of the UK General Data Protection Regulation (UK GDPR) and the Data Protection Act
        2018, the data controller for BracketMath is Luke Bell, contactable at
        <a href="mailto:[email protected]">[email protected]</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>2. Calculator inputs (the important bit)</h2>
      <p>
        Every calculator on BracketMath is a static page that loads a small amount of JavaScript into your
        browser. When you type a number into a calculator (your salary, dividend, pension contribution,
        age, retirement age, etc.) and click "Calculate", the calculation happens entirely on your device.
        Your inputs <strong>never travel across the network</strong>. They are never logged, stored, sold,
        shared, or seen by us, by Cloudflare, by any analytics provider, or by anyone else.
      </p>
      <p>
        Refresh the page and your inputs are gone forever, even from your own browser (unless we add an
        explicit "save" feature in future — which we would communicate clearly).
      </p>

      <h2>3. Cookies</h2>
      <p>
        BracketMath does not set any first-party cookies. There is no cookie banner because there is nothing
        to consent to. The site is statically generated and served via Cloudflare's edge network; Cloudflare
        may set a strictly necessary security cookie (`__cf_bm`) to mitigate bot traffic — this is exempt
        from the consent requirement under the Privacy and Electronic Communications Regulations
        (PECR) Regulation 6(4)(b) because it is "strictly necessary" for the service you have requested
        (delivering the website). It cannot be used to track you across other sites.
      </p>

      <h2>4. Analytics</h2>
      <p>
        We use <strong>Cloudflare Web Analytics</strong> to count page views and broad geographic
        information (typically: country, sometimes region). This is a cookieless, privacy-preserving
        analytics service. No personal data, no IP addresses, no device fingerprints, and no cross-site
        tracking identifiers are collected. Cloudflare's documentation of the service is available at
        <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/web-analytics/" rel="noopener">cloudflare.com/web-analytics</a>.
      </p>
      <p>
        We do <strong>not</strong> use Google Analytics, Meta/Facebook Pixel, TikTok Pixel, Twitter Pixel,
        Hotjar, FullStory, Microsoft Clarity, or any session-replay or fingerprinting analytics services.
      </p>

      <h2>5. Server logs</h2>
      <p>
        Cloudflare, as our hosting and CDN provider, processes basic technical metadata (HTTP request
        details, IP address, user agent) for the purpose of serving the page to you and protecting the
        site against denial-of-service and abusive bot traffic. Cloudflare's privacy practices for this
        processing are documented at
        <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/privacypolicy/" rel="noopener">cloudflare.com/privacypolicy</a>.
        We do not receive, store, or have access to these raw logs.
      </p>

      <h2>6. Affiliate links</h2>
      <p>
        Some outbound links on this site are affiliate links (see the <a href="/disclaimer">disclaimer</a>
        for full details). When you click an affiliate link, the destination third-party network or
        merchant (e.g. Awin, Impact.com, or the brand directly) may set a cookie on your browser to
        attribute a future sign-up or purchase to BracketMath. That cookie is set by the third party,
        not by us, and is governed by their privacy policy — not this one. If you do not want to be tracked
        by a third party after clicking, you can right-click the affiliate link, copy the destination URL,
        and visit the merchant directly without the tracking parameter.
      </p>

      <h2>7. Email contact</h2>
      <p>
        If you email <a href="mailto:[email protected]">[email protected]</a> we will, of course,
        see your email address and your message. We use Gmail (operated by Google) to receive and read
        these emails. We don't add you to any list, don't share your message with anyone, and delete the
        thread once the matter is resolved. Google's processing of email is governed by their own
        privacy policy.
      </p>

      <h2>8. Your rights under UK GDPR</h2>
      <p>
        Because BracketMath does not collect or store personal data about you, there is, in practice,
        nothing for us to disclose, rectify, port, or delete. If you have nevertheless emailed us and
        wish for the thread to be deleted, email us and we will delete it. You also have the right to
        complain to the Information Commissioner's Office (<a href="https://ico.org.uk" rel="noopener">ico.org.uk</a>)
        if you believe we have mishandled your data.
      </p>

      <h2>9. Changes to this policy</h2>
      <p>
        If we materially change what we do with data — for example, by adding a newsletter sign-up,
        a contact form, or a user account system — we will update this page and note the change in the
        "Last updated" line below. Cosmetic clarifications won't be flagged but won't change the substance.
      </p>

      <p class="text-sm text-[color:var(--color-ink-light)] mt-12">
        Last updated: 12 May 2026.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
